Tea Eggs
Difficulty: 1
Makes: 6 eggs

Ingredients: 
6 eggs
1 tbsp Chinese dark soy sauce
1 tbsp Chinese light soy sauce
1 tbsp salt
2 tbsp oolong or Iron Goddess tea leaves

In a small pot, hard boil the eggs. Wash the cooked eggs in cold water, then use a spoon to gently crack the shells of each egg. Do not remove the shells. Add new water to the pot and place the eggs back in, adding the soy sauces, salt, and tea leaves. Bring to a boil again. Eggs can be kept in sauce to strengthen the flavor until served.
